<Header HeaderType="HeaderTypes.H3">Navbar</Header>

<Paragraph>
    The idea behind this component is for it to be flexible while also being opinionated for simple use cases.
    Any navbar to be used must be able to look properly when being used on mobile as well as on desktop.
</Paragraph>

<Header HeaderType="HeaderTypes.H4">Parameters</Header>

<Table CssClass="mb-10">
    <TableHead>
        <TableHeader>Parameter</TableHeader>
        <TableHeader>Optional?</TableHeader>
        <TableHeader>Type</TableHeader>
        <TableHeader>Description</TableHeader>
    </TableHead>
    <TableBody>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>Color</TableCell>
            <TableCell>No</TableCell>
            <TableCell>NavigationColors</TableCell>
            <TableCell>Allows you to decide a background color based on the config for the library.</TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>BrandingFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>No</TableCell>
            <TableCell>RenderFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>This is fragment is meant to contain any element that is left aligned where branding is in most navbars.</TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>MobileNavigationFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>No</TableCell>
            <TableCell>RenderFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>
                The mobile counterpart to NavigationFragment.
                By common convention, it displays only when the hamburger menu is open and it is displayed right below the navbar in mobile.
            </TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>NavigationFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>No</TableCell>
            <TableCell>RenderFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>
                The navigation fragment is meant for links and navigational elements for the application or website.
                As is common convention, it aligns all elements to the right of the sidebar.
            </TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>MobileNavigationFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>No</TableCell>
            <TableCell>RenderFragment</TableCell>
            <TableCell>
                The mobile counterpart to NavigationFragment.
                By common convention, it displays only when the hamburger menu is open and it is displayed right below the navbar in mobile.
            </TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>OnMobileMenuClick</TableCell>
            <TableCell>Yes</TableCell>
            <TableCell>EventCallback</TableCell>
            <TableCell>
                An optional event that can be added to the clicking of the hamburger menu.
                This does not override the common behaviour of opening the MobileNavigationFragment, instead it just allows you to add additional capacity to said action should it be needed.
            </TableCell>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <TableCell>HasMobileMenu</TableCell>
            <TableCell>Yes</TableCell>
            <TableCell>boolean</TableCell>
            <TableCell>
                True by default. This parameter is meant to be used only when you want to disable the mobile menu if you have no need for it.
            </TableCell>
        </tr>
    </TableBody>
</Table>

